The paper deals with information-theoretic understanding of sparse sampling and sensing, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses signal processing (cs.SP) and machine learning (cs.MM) techniques for sparse sensing and sampling. The use of state-dependent channels suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.SI). Finally, the paper derives tight bounds on information rates and performance, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
